  "text": "In practice, dead spots or coverage holes usually cause disconnection (i.e., WLAN and 3G are not available). In this situation, a huge queue backlog even queue instability might be caused, because the mobile application cannot be offloaded to cloud any more. In fact, this problem can be tackled by making the cloud services temporarily stopped. We will treat this case as a joint optimization of local execution and transmitting cost in the future. Moreover, MCC faces the channel's competition problem, when several users offload the mobile applications to cloud at the same time. This problem has been treated in [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] and is beyond the scope of this paper. In this paper, we only consider that a mobile user offloads mobile application from MD to cloud.",
